passages.text:
//You've travelled up and away from the city proper to a house in the hills to speak with him. 

As you open the doors, you see him standing before you, silhouetted against the sun beaming on the city skyline.//

[[The Moneymaker speaks]]

//He looks down at his knife, twirling it in his hand.//

'You're so willing to take a life... The idea comes so easily to you.'

//He looks up.//

'But don't understand the value of a life, do you?'

//He looks back down.//

'Our lives are meaningless, of course. Only until we die, do our lives mean anything at all. Only in death do people give us value.'

//He tosses a satchel on the ground with a thud, a gentle clink of coins.//

'Tell me something,' he asks.

[[Yes?->Do you know anyone who has died?]]

'I suppose.'

'But even then... Many more of you might not succeed. You'll have invested in your journey to only end up coming back empty handed.'

//He picks through some old relics.//

'Not a hero.'

//He holds up a carbonite shield. //

//And puts it down.//

'Not a champion.'

//He holds up a trophy.//

//And puts it down.//

'And many of you will realize, that you're just a commoner, like the rest of us...'

[[I don't think I am a commoner->Not a commoner]]
[[I need to try to be a hero before I settle with being common->Not a commoner]]
[[There's nothing wrong with being a commoner->Am a commoner]]

'The worst part is...'

//She turns her head down.//

'Not only knowing that you're just something for others to capture and tie up against your will and be locked away. 

//She shakes her chains.//

'...Not only knowing that you're just something prettied up for someone else to get, to feel entitled to, like a doggie biscuit.'

'It's...'

//She turns looks to the sky.//

'Not knowing how to be anything else.'

[[You don't know how to be anything else?]]

//You take the cup and have a few quiet sips with her.//

'Ah... It's good to be able to share a nice cup of tea with someone, isn't it?'

//You taste the druidic herbs and nutrosupplements.//

//Her smile reaches her eyes. It seems she hasn't done this in a long time.//

[[Anyway, let's talk about him...]]

~End~



