body {
	background-color: black;
}
	tw-passage {
		color: white;
	}

</style>}

(set: $visited to $visited + 1)
[[Return to Main Menu->Character select]]

'Hm.'

//A pause.//

//He smiles.//

'Good!' //he says pointing at you.// 'You did your reading! I like you!'

//He clears his throat.//

'Sure, that 0.1% of adventurers who'd do anything to get more adventuring made up 90% of the market. But that's their own choice isn't it?'

'So yeah, part of our business strategy was to focus on that key market and make sure we kept those people... //highly engaged//.'

[['Engaged' is just a euphemism isn't it?.]]

//He picks up his glass, and looks down at it, swishing around his drink in the ice, other hand in his pocket.'//


'Y'know it's easy to be young and idealistic...'

'Believe it or not, I was like that too.'

//He points to an old holophoto of himself. The hologram shows a younger version of him, vibrant, smiling, certainly thinner and with more hair.//

'But then I started facing questions that I never thought I'd have to answer.'

[[What kind of questions?]]

'Heroes, eh?'

//She turns and stares at you straight in the eye.//

'Do you think they're doing me a favor?'

//She looks out the window.//

'I see them out there. They don't seem like they're worried about me at all.

'They're just focused on having their fun and going on their adventures...'

//She shakes her chains.//

'I just happen to be at the end of it.'

[[People aren't here for you...->People aren't here for me]]

//He takes a sip.//

'So you're running a company, things are going well, it's growing a lot, you're hiring more people. Business is booming. You're getting a lot of attention.'

//He points to a shelf filled with trophies and articles.
--#1 Up-and-Coming Startup--
--Best Company to Invest in Now--
//

'And people love working there. Love it! You'll walk down the hall and people will say working for you is the best job they've had in their lives.'

'There's this funny thing where people give each other high fives in the hallway and say, //"Hey buddy!"// it's the silliest thing!'

//He chuckles.//

'Boy...'

'On top of that the family is doing great.'

[[How's the family doing?->Family is doing great]]

'Boy, that's cold...'

//He takes a sip.//

//A chuckle.//

'...It's what I did, though.'

[[You did that??]]

//Through her tears she says...//

'That's how I chose to remember him. A baby, in my arms... Forever and always.'


[[It's quiet for a while...]]

//Through her tears she says...//

'That's how his father chose to remember him. A man, standing tall... Forever and always.'



[[It's quiet for a while...]]

//She gives a faint smile and holds your hand, holding back her tears.//

'That's what I had wished too.'

[[Why'd you wish that?]]

'My daughter.'

//He strokes his chin and stops pacing.//

[[Your daughter?!]]

//He looks up from his glass as he takes a sip.//

'So... Tell me something.'

'So the world died, right?'

//When he says this, you know he means when the markets fell and the Old Kingdom became the New.//

'Ask any of these other people you're going around interviewing, every single one of them was struggling through that, trying to survive.'

'Well...'

'What if I were to tell you, while people were dying in the streets and losing their homes, I, my family, and my employees were living it up, and we did better than anyone...'


'Because we //profited// off of it.'

//He's nodding his head.//

[[What?! You...]]

//He sets down his glass on the table and just stares at you for a bit.//








'Hm.'


[[Is that all you have to say?->I was like you once]]

//He stares at you for a bit.//







'Hm. You give me more credit than a lot of people.'


[[But what you did was pretty monstrous...->I was like you once]]

'So.'

//She takes a deep breath.//

'So it was either be a princess and be whatever they wanted...'

'Or the street.'

//She looks at a bug on the windowsill.//

'And I didn't want the street.'

//She flicks the bug out the window.//

'So here I am... a //beautiful//...'

'//Little//...'



'//Fool//.'



//She's quiet for a time.//

[[The Princess asks]]

'Yup, the numbers checked out. The whole world was going to die... And we were seeing it in slow motion.'

//He takes out a gold coin out of his pocket.//

'See this?' 

//He's holding it and pointing to a large skyscraper out the window.//

'You see that bank? It's the biggest bank in the kingdom.'

'This goddamn coin was worth several kingdoms more than that whole goddamn bank would be worth in the next business cycle.'

//He puts the coin back in his pocket, shakes his head, and claps his arms at his side in defeat.//

'And it's not just the fault of us in the capitals, you know?'

[[How wasn't it your fault?]]

//
You make your way to a cabin deep in the woods. The forest is rich here, with trees climbing over 100 meters towards the heavens, moss growing on rocks and logs, the mountains loom in the distance, you hear the gentle rushing of river streams.

You meet an old man, smiling through his beard from ear to ear. 

You take a seat.
//

[[The Legend speaks]]

'Alright then.'

'Everyone must live their own life.'

//She closes her eyes.//

'From one to the next.'

//She relaxes her body and sits, breathing for a while.//

[[Wait until she's back->Back from breathing]]
